00:04:49.000 --> 00:04:52.430
So how does this relate
to the constitution?

00:04:52.430 --> 00:04:56.210
And why does this take
up a chapter in our book?

00:04:56.210 --> 00:05:01.180
The answer goes back
to December 2010

00:05:01.180 --> 00:05:06.680
when the House passed legislation
that would have legalized

00:05:06.680 --> 00:05:14.360
or normalized the presence in the
United States of children brought

00:05:14.360 --> 00:05:18.080
into the United States
by their parents

00:05:18.080 --> 00:05:25.830
and would have given them basically
a safe haven in the United States.

00:05:25.830 --> 00:05:32.400
Congress is bicameral and we spend
a great number of pages in our book

00:05:32.400 --> 00:05:36.460
on the fact that Congress
consists of two separate houses.

00:05:36.460 --> 00:05:38.330
So getting through the
House wasn't good enough.

00:05:38.330 --> 00:05:40.270
It has to go through the Senate.

00:05:40.270 --> 00:05:42.330
What happened in the Senate?

00:05:42.330 --> 00:05:46.950
Well, as a matter of fact,
a majority of the Senate,

00:05:46.950 --> 00:05:49.510
with members from both parties,

00:05:49.510 --> 00:05:53.570
supported the so-called
Dream Act bill.

00:05:53.570 --> 00:06:00.100
But a majority isn't good enough
thanks to Rule 22 of the Senate

00:06:00.100 --> 00:06:04.420
that requires a super-majority
in order

00:06:04.420 --> 00:06:06.820
for bills to come up to a vote.

00:06:06.820 --> 00:06:14.190
So the key vote in the Senate in
December of 2010 was whether or not

00:06:14.190 --> 00:06:16.660
to go forth with legislation.

00:06:16.660 --> 00:06:19.540
The vote was 55 to 45.

00:06:19.540 --> 00:06:24.360
You might think that in a country
that calls itself a democracy

00:06:24.360 --> 00:06:28.730
that would be good
enough to go to a vote.

00:06:28.730 --> 00:06:35.120
Well it isn't because Rule 22
says you have to have 60 votes

00:06:35.120 --> 00:06:39.490
and 60 is more than 55, obviously.

00:06:39.490 --> 00:06:44.720
This can be traced back to
an obscure but important part

00:06:44.720 --> 00:06:48.070
of the constitution
that gives each house

00:06:48.070 --> 00:06:51.620
of Congress the ability
to set its own rules.

00:06:51.620 --> 00:06:55.770
And so one of the rules the
Senate has established is

00:06:55.770 --> 00:07:00.030
to require a super-majority
to get a vote.

00:07:00.030 --> 00:07:05.070
